page.title: 05SOME OLD HOUSES IN THE AREA
page.content: Natalie's house on Middle Hill, was built in 1930 by Walter Wolsey. It is semi detached of soft Norfolk brick, made locally. It was used by the groom at the White House. Alexander says his house at Doctor's Corner is the oldest in the village.It has seventeen rooms, a stable block and one acre of land. The oldest part is built of flint and altered in Victorian times. It was a doctor's House for 120 years. White's 'Norfolk'lists the owner in 1865 as Thomas Prangley,surgeon. Then came Dr. Spurrell, Dr. Barton and finally Dr. Eddy. The house is now lived in by 3 generations of Alexander's family. His parents design and hand print cards. James tells us in Wickmere the school is now a private house owned by 2 musical ladies who give concerts.
